summary:
The Security Council,
Welcoming the Secretary-General's report on the UN operation in Cyprus, 
particularly the call to address the humanitarian issue of missing persons urgently,
Noting the Government of Cyprus's agreement to extend the UN Peacekeeping Force,
Welcoming efforts to sensitize peacekeeping personnel on HIV/AIDS and communicable diseases,

1. Reaffirms all relevant Cyprus resolutions, particularly 1251 (1999);
2. Extends UNFICYP's mandate until 15 December 2001;
3. Requests a report by 1 December 2001 on the implementation;
4. Urges the Turkish Cypriot side and Turkish forces to rescind restrictions on UNFICYP and restore the military status quo at Strovilia;
5. Decides to remain seized of the matter.
